benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails - Add account email

covered: Happy path and variations for 201 responses with a JSON array of AccountEmail objects and Location header (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05)
Header handling coverage including mandatory and optional headers (TC02, TC05) and missing header scenario (TC13) and unauthorized access (TC14)
AccountId validation coverage (TC07 invalid format, TC08 missing, TC09 non-existent)
Invalid payload coverage (TC10 malformed JSON, TC11 missing required fields, TC12 invalid email, TC17 empty body, TC06 extra fields)
Edge cases for payload size and extra parameters (TC16 large payload, TC18 extra query parameters)
Server availability and performance edge cases (TC15 503 service down, TC19 degraded DB/performance) and recovery (TC25)
Security tests (TC23 SQL injection, TC24 XSS)
Concurrency and integration (TC20 concurrent requests, TC26 downstream system propagation)
Compatibility and regression (TC21 unicode handling, TC22 backward compatibility)
gaps: Duplicate submission / idempotency tests (no explicit test for adding the same email twice)
Rate limiting / throttling tests (no explicit rate-limiting scenarios)
Internal server error (500) specific tests (only 503 covered; no 500 test case)
Dedicated tests for missing X-Killbill-Reason and missing X-Killbill-Comment individually (only CreatedBy header absence tested in TC13)
Explicit 429 Too Many Requests tests for rate limiting (missing)
recommendations: Add a duplicate submission test to verify idempotency or conflict handling (409/duplicate behavior)
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests (to confirm proper handling under high load)
Add caching tests (ETag, Cache-Control) to validate caching behavior
Add a 500 Internal Server Error scenario to differentiate from 503 service unavailability
Add dedicated tests for missing Reason and missing Comment headers when they are absent or malformed, in addition to missing CreatedBy (TC13)
Consider adding 429 tests for rate limiting, and more explicit error messages for common failures to improve accessibility
